cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

The paper focuses on object localization in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of learned knowledge and probability distributions suggests a machine learning approach (cs.AI), and the iterative sampling and adaptation of distributions suggest a reinforcement learning or active learning approach (cs.LG). The use of context and semantic structure also suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) as relevant sub-categories.
